fileread - reads and displays the content of a text file

Description:
The 'fileread' command opens a specified file and prints its content to the terminal. It only works with text files; binary files are rejected. If no file is specified, or if the file cannot be read, an error message is shown.

Usage:
fileread <file_name>

Examples:
fileread notes.txt
fileread # Error: Invalid name provided.
fileread binary.dat # Error: Not a text file.
